(13,'College Dropout',  2004, 'Hip Hop', 25.00, 'Mint', 'The College Dropout is the debut studio album by American rapper and producer Kanye West. It was released on February 10, 2004, by Roc-A-Fella Records and Def Jam Recordings. Prior to the album, West had received praise for his production work for rappers such as Jay-Z and Talib Kweli, but faced difficulty being accepted as an artist in his own right by figures in the music industry. Nonetheless, it was West''s desire to release a solo album that led to him to begin work on The College Dropout. The album includes songs that were produced by West, alongside other record producers such as Just Blaze, The Neptunes, and DJ Toomp.'),
(14,'The Blueprint', 2001, 'Hip Hop', 25.00, 'Mint', 'The Blueprint is the sixth studio album by American rapper Jay-Z. It was released on September 11, 2001, by Roc-A-Fella Records and Def Jam Recordings. The album is also famous for both its producers Kanye West and Just Blaze, as well as its departure from the distinctive sound that Jay-Z himself and Timbaland had developed in the late 1990s. The Blueprint received universal acclaim from music critics, with praise being directed at Jay-Z''s lyricism and the production. It is considered one of Jay-Z''s best albums and has also been labeled as one of the greatest hip-hop albums of all time.'),
(15,'The Marshall Mathers LP',  2000, 'Hip Hop', 25.00, 'Mint', 'The Marshall Mathers LP is the third studio album by American rapper Eminem. It was released on May 23, 2000, by Aftermath Entertainment, Interscope Records, and Eminem''s newly founded label, Shady Records in the United States, and on September 11, 2000, by Polydor Records in the United Kingdom. The album was produced mostly by Dr. Dre and Eminem, along with The 45 King, the Bass Brothers, and Melle Mel'),
(9,'Midnight mMrauders', 1993, 'Hip Hop', 25.00, 'Mint', 'Midnight Marauders is the third studio album by American hip hop group A Tribe Called Quest, released on November 9, 1993, by Jive Records. Recording sessions for the album occurred at Battery Studios, Platinum Island Studios and Scorcerer Sound in New York City. Its production was mainly handled by the group themselves, with additional tracks provided by Skeff Anselm, Large Professor and the Ummah.'),
